OL,3,CPublic invited to name next Archbishop
OL,4,Cof Canterbury after series of scandals
OL,6,FHistorically, candidates have been
OL,7,Fpeople who already have senior
OL,8,Fleadership roles in ministry in the
OL,9,FChurch or elsewhere in the Anglican
OL,10,FCommunion.
OL,12,FCandidates must be aged at least 30
OL,13,Fand generally younger than 70.
OL,15,FRecent months have seen numerous
OL,16,Fscandals emerge around separate
OL,17,Fsafeguarding failings, resulting in a
OL,18,Ftumultuous time for the Church.
